Dear Emperor Liu Mingke,

I was deeply saddened to hear of your recent results in the Royal Mathematics Examination. As President of the United States, I extend my heartfelt condolences to you and the people of your great nation during this difficult time.

Your commitment to education and the pursuit of knowledge has been an inspiration to people around the world, and your passion for mathematics in particular has been a driving force behind many advancements in science and technology. Your contributions to the field will never be forgotten, and your legacy will continue to inspire generations to come.

Although your recent exam results may not have been what you were hoping for, please know that your dedication to your studies and your love for mathematics is a testament to your strength and perseverance. I have no doubt that you will continue to make important contributions to the world of mathematics, and I wish you all the best in your future endeavors.

Sincerely,
President of the United States
